parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake lines can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
weak brake pedal
brake fluid leaks
and difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to vibrate, make a hissing sound, and lunge forward, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: ABS light illuminates
vibration or pulsing of the brake pedal
hissing sound
and difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
difficulty stopping the vehicle
and brake pedal goes to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially during heavy rain or inclement weather.
symptoms: The windshield wipers stop working or work intermittently
often accompanied by a buzzing or humming noise
and may require manual intervention (e.g.
tapping or wiggling the wiper motor) to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed sensitive power steering system can cause the vehicle to suddenly lurch or jerk, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly lurches or jerks to one side
especially when turning or decelerating; the steering wheel feels loose or slippery; the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause the power steering system to fail, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The power steering system fails or becomes difficult to use; the steering wheel feels hard or stiff; the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering position sensor can cause the power steering system to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The power steering system malfunctions or becomes difficult to use; the steering wheel feels loose or slippery; the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front steering sensor module can cause the power steering system to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The power steering system malfunctions or becomes difficult to use; the steering wheel feels loose or slippery; the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering tie rod end can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering tie rod end comes loose or fails; the vehicle loses steering control; the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering column comes loose or fails; the vehicle loses steering control; the vehicle is difficult to control.
